    • writeValue

      void writeValue(Row row)
      Writes a row to an SQL table
      Parameters:
      row - Row of data to write
      Implementation Note:
      This is very important for server performance. When writing to a database outside of the onDisable method will slow down the server if your database is not already hosted locally. This also applies to the onDisable method but data must be written immediately before the plugin is shut off so that someone stopping the server doesn't lose data.

    • commit

      void commit(boolean async)
      Since writeValue(Row) and writeValue(Object...) use an SQL batch statement to execute writing (in order to save performance) you must use this to commit the changes to the database. Not committing will lead to data being lost.
      Parameters:
      async - Whether to run on async thread or main thread. True indicates running on an async thread
      See Also:
      • (Row) for implementation of batching.
      Implementation Note:
      When using SQL table handlers you can also use ISQLTableHandler.writeToDB() to commit automatically.

    • commit

      void commit()
      Since writeValue(Row) and writeValue(Object...) use an SQL batch statement to execute writing (in order to save performance) you must use this to commit the changes to the database. Not committing will lead to data being lost.
      See Also:
      • SQLTable.writeValue for implementation of batching.
      Implementation Note:
      When using SQL table handlers you can also use ISQLTableHandler.writeToDB() to commit automatically.
